     <h3><strong>EVENT DETAIL</strong> </h3>
      <P>DIBI FESTIVAL</P>
      <P>The Dibi Festival is an annual celebration in Mali, showcasing the country's culture, music, dance, and traditional cuisine. It takes its name from the traditional Malian dish "dibi", a specialty of grilled meat. Usually held during the dry season, the festival includes concerts, dance demonstrations, culinary competitions of meat grilling, local craft exhibitions, and tastings of traditional dishes. It also offers visitors a </P>
     <p>The Dibi Festival welcomes a wide variety of participants, both local and international, from different regions of Mali and sometimes even from other countries. Here is a description of the main participants and the details of the festival:</p>
      <p>Residents of surrounding towns and villages: Local residents actively participate in the festival, contributing to its cultural richness and authenticity.
Malian artists and musicians: Traditional music groups, dancers, and other local artists perform at the festival, offering visitors a glimpse into Mali's artistic diversity.
Chefs & Grillers: Grilling masters, known locally as "grilladins," prepare the delicious ones </p>
